Howto run the html examples with persistent http connection:
============================================================

1. Set the DocumentRoot of your web server to this directory
   for Apache e.g.:

   DocumentRoot "/home/ruff/xmlBlaster/demo/html"


2. Add the servlet to you servlet env, with jserv in zone.properties:

   servlet.SystemInfo.code=html.systemInfo.SystemInfo


3. Use the 'make all' or 'build.bat deploy_ear' or copy manually:
   cp -r  ../../src/java/org/xmlBlaster/protocol/http/javascript  javascript
   cp -r  ../../src/java/org/xmlBlaster/protocol/http/persistentWindow  persistentWindow
   cp -r  ../../doc/howto/xmlBlaster.css  xmlBlaster.css


4. Start xmlBlaster

   jaco org.xmlBlaster.Main


5. Start a publisher, so that we have some dynamic data:

   java html.systemInfo.SystemInfoPublisher


6. Start you browser

   http://localhost/systemInfo/systemInfo.html?ActionType=login&xmlBlaster.loginName=martin&xmlBlaster.passwd=secret


Start it in the background on Linux:
====================================

   java org.xmlBlaster.Main -Xms12M -Xmx32M -logFile /tmp/xmlBlaster.log  -useKeyboard false  > /tmp/xmlBlaster.log 2>&1 &

   #jserv > /tmp/jserv.log 2>&1 &
   CLASSPATH=$CLASSPATH:/usr/lib/apache/ApacheJServ.jar
   java -Xms12M -Xmx32M org.apache.jserv.JServ /etc/httpd/conf/jserv/jserv.properties > /tmp/jserv.log 2>&1 &

   java html.systemInfo.SystemInfoPublisher -info false > /tmp/SystemInfoPublisher.log 2>&1 &


Using tomcat 4.0 serlvet enginge (http:jakarta.apache.org):
===========================================================

export CATALINA_HOME=$HOME/jakarta-tomcat-4.0
export PATH=$CATALINA_HOME/bin:$PATH
startup.sh   (add "tail -f $CATALINA_HOME/logs/catalina.out" to the end of this script)

For deployment see WEB-INF/web.xml

http://localhost:8080/xmlBlaster/SystemInfo
